    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Open a webpage with linked images (i.e. https://en.wikipedia.org/).\r\n2. Long tap on a linked image.\r\n3. Rotate the device and landscape mode.\r\n4. Scroll to the bottom of the context menu.\r\n5. Scroll up and down and observe the dark purple section of the context menu.\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe dark purple section of the context menu should be static when scrolling on Landscape mode.\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThe dark purple section of the context menu is dynamic, and can be hidden when scrolling on Landscape mode.\r\n### Device information\r\n\r\n* Android device: Google Pixel 6 (Android 12), LG G7 fit (Android 8.1.0), Samsung Galaxy note 8 (Android 9).\r\nNote that the issue is not encountered on Lenovo Tab M10 (Android 10).\r\n\r\n* Focus version:  latest Nightly from 03/07.\r\nReproducible on 98.1.0, 98.1.1 and 97.3.0.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/157066484-f529e29e-9119-4035-afd8-780ae395a413.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
